com.urbancode.ubuild.scripting.wrappers
Class SourceAnalyticReportWrapper

java.lang.Object
  com.urbancode.ubuild.scripting.wrappers.SourceAnalyticReportWrapper

public class SourceAnalyticReportWrapper
extends java.lang.Object

Scripting class to give limited access to SourceAnalyticReport information. This is exposed through methods on the buildLife object in notification scripts.

Examples:

To get the list of findings for a source analytic report: 

    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports().get(0).getFindings()
To get the id of a source analytic report: 
    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports().get(0).getId()
To get the name of a source analytic report: 
    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports().get(0).getName()
To get the type of a source analytic report: 
    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports().get(0).getType()
To get the URL for a source analytic report: 
    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports().get(0).getUrl()
If you are using velocity scripts for Notification Templates, you don't have to use the full method name for getters: 
    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports().get(0).Findings
    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports().get(0).Id
    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports().get(0).Name
    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports().get(0).Type
    buildLife.getSourceAnalyticReports().get(0).Url
